.Dd February 24, 2026
.Dt CONTACTD 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm contactd
.Nd minimal CardDAV daemon using SQLite
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl hV
.Op Fl l Ar addr
.Op Fl p Ar port
.Op Fl d Ar path
.Op Fl -base-url Ar url
.Op Fl -log-level Ar level
.Op Fl -log-format Ar fmt
.Op Fl -trust-proxy-headers
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
serves a CardDAV endpoint over HTTP and stores data in SQLite.
It is intended to run behind a reverse proxy that terminates TLS.
.Pp
The daemon provides a single health endpoint,
.Pa /health ,
which performs an HTTP + SQLite check.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Print usage and exit.
.It Fl V , Fl -version
Print version and exit.
.It Fl l , Fl -listen-addr Ar addr
Listen address (for example
.Sq :8080
or
.Sq 127.0.0.1:8080 ) .
.It Fl p , Fl -port Ar port
Convenience shorthand for listening on
.Sq :PORT .
Cannot be combined with
.Fl l .
.It Fl d , Fl -db-path Ar path
SQLite database path.
Default:
.Pa /var/db/contactd.db .
.It Fl -base-url Ar url
Public base URL used for redirects (for example
.Pa /.well-known/carddav ) .
.It Fl -log-level Ar level
Log level:
.Cm debug ,
.Cm info ,
.Cm warn ,
or
.Cm error .
.It Fl -log-format Ar fmt
Log format:
.Cm text
(daemon-style) or
.Cm json .
.It Fl -trust-proxy-headers
Trust
.Dq X-Forwarded-*
and related proxy headers for access-log remote address handling.
Enable only behind a trusted reverse proxy.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
Configuration precedence is:
flags > environment > defaults.
.Pp
Common variables:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev CONTACTD_LISTEN_ADDR
Listen address.
.It Ev PORT
Fallback port if
.Ev CONTACTD_LISTEN_ADDR
is unset.
.It Ev CONTACTD_DB_PATH
SQLite database path.
.It Ev CONTACTD_BASE_URL
Public base URL for redirects.
.It Ev CONTACTD_LOG_LEVEL
Log level.
.It Ev CONTACTD_LOG_FORMAT
Log format
.Pq Cm text Ns / Ns Cm json .
.It Ev CONTACTD_TRUST_PROXY_HEADERS
Trust proxy headers.
.It Ev CONTACTD_REQUEST_MAX_BYTES
Request body limit.
.It Ev CONTACTD_VCARD_MAX_BYTES
Maximum stored vCard size.
.It Ev CONTACTD_USERS
Bootstrap user seed (empty DB only, unless forced).
.It Ev CONTACTD_FORCE_SEED
Re-apply seed users even when the DB already has users.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa /var/db/contactd.db
Default SQLite database path.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Run on localhost:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
contactd -l 127.0.0.1:8080 -d /var/db/contactd.db
.Ed
.It
Check daemon health:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/health
.Ed
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr contactctl 8
